./PRODUCT_SPEC.md:5:A REST API for managing bookmarks with folder organization, user authentication, and pagination. Built with TypeScript, Express, and better-sqlite3.
./PRODUCT_SPEC.md:11:- **Bookmark**: A saved URL with title, optional description, timestamps, and zero or more tags
./PRODUCT_SPEC.md:12:- **Folder**: A named collection of bookmarks
./PRODUCT_SPEC.md:13:- **User**: An authenticated account that owns bookmarks and folders
./PRODUCT_SPEC.md:14:- **Tag**: A user-owned label that can be attached to many bookmarks
./PRODUCT_SPEC.md:21:#### Bookmarks (after auth: scoped to authenticated user)
./PRODUCT_SPEC.md:22:- `POST /bookmarks` — Create a bookmark (requires: url, title)
./PRODUCT_SPEC.md:23:- `GET /bookmarks` — List all bookmarks (paginated after T6)
./PRODUCT_SPEC.md:24:- `GET /bookmarks/:id` — Get single bookmark
./PRODUCT_SPEC.md:25:- `PUT /bookmarks/:id` — Update a bookmark
./PRODUCT_SPEC.md:26:- `DELETE /bookmarks/:id` — Delete a bookmark
./PRODUCT_SPEC.md:28:- Bookmark responses include `tags`, an array of tag objects.
./PRODUCT_SPEC.md:29:- `GET /bookmarks?tag=work` filters to bookmarks tagged `work`.
./PRODUCT_SPEC.md:30:- `GET /bookmarks?tags=work,docs` filters to bookmarks tagged with all listed tag names.
./PRODUCT_SPEC.md:31:- `GET /bookmarks?q=docs` searches the authenticated user's bookmarks by title, URL, description, folder name, and tag names. Empty `q` behaves like no search. Queries longer than 200 characters return `400`. Search results keep the paginated envelope and are ranked by exact title match, title prefix match, title substring match, then other field matches with deterministic tie ordering.
./PRODUCT_SPEC.md:33:#### Folders
./PRODUCT_SPEC.md:34:- `POST /folders` — Create a folder (requires: name)
./PRODUCT_SPEC.md:35:- `GET /folders` — List all folders
./PRODUCT_SPEC.md:36:- `GET /folders/:id` — Get folder with its bookmarks
./PRODUCT_SPEC.md:37:- `PUT /folders/:id` — Update folder name
./PRODUCT_SPEC.md:38:- `DELETE /folders/:id` — Delete folder (bookmarks become unfoldered)
./PRODUCT_SPEC.md:40:#### Tags
./PRODUCT_SPEC.md:41:- `POST /tags` — Create a tag (requires: name)
./PRODUCT_SPEC.md:42:- `GET /tags` — List current user's tags
./PRODUCT_SPEC.md:43:- `PUT /tags/:id` — Rename a tag
./PRODUCT_SPEC.md:44:- `DELETE /tags/:id` — Delete a tag and unlink it from bookmarks
./PRODUCT_SPEC.md:53:- Bookmark `url` must be a valid URL
./PRODUCT_SPEC.md:63:- `GET /bookmarks?page=1&limit=20`
./PRODUCT_SPEC.md:74:- **Testing**: Vitest
